    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-03-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <head>228. Memorandum From the Acting Director of the Arms Control and Disarmament
                    Agency (<persName corresp="#p_FAS2" type="from">Fisher</persName>) to Secretary
                    of State <persName corresp="#p_RD3" type="to">Rusk</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d228fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 383, <gloss target="#t_ACDA1"
                            >ACDA</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_D1">D</gloss> Files: <gloss
                            target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 77 <gloss target="#t_A1">A</gloss> 52,
                        Memoranda to the Secretary of State, 1968. Confidential. The source text
                        bears the concurrences of <persName corresp="#p_LJM2">Leddy</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_PH7">Pollack</persName>, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_TGF1">Tape</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-03-15">March 15, 1968</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_EURATOM1">Euratom</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_IAEA1"
                            >IAEA</gloss> Safeguards Agreement (<gloss target="#t_U1"
                        >U</gloss>)</item>
                </list>
                <p>As you know, an essential element for the success of the <gloss target="#t_NPT1"
                        >NPT</gloss> is the achievement of the required safeguards agreements,
                    including one between the European Community and the <gloss target="#t_IAEA1"
                        >IAEA</gloss>. We have already made known to both organizations our
                    willingness to assist them in any appropriate way to reach agreement.</p>
                <p>To formulate and coordinate a program for such U.S. assistance, and to provide
                    continuing guidance in achieving our objective, I recommend that we establish a
                    special task force, which would include representatives of the Department of
                    State offices most directly concerned (<gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss> and
                        <gloss target="#t_SCI1">SCI</gloss>) along with <gloss target="#t_AEC1"
                        >AEC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_ACDA1">ACDA</gloss>. The task force will
                    maintain close consultation with Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SHDW1"
                        >Smyth</persName> and Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SJR3"
                        >Schaetzel</persName>.</p>
                <p>I recommend that we designate as chairman of this task force <persName
                        corresp="#p_KMB1">Myron B. Kratzer</persName>, the <gloss target="#t_AEC1"
                        >AEC</gloss>’s Assistant General Manager for International Activities. I
                    believe Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KMB1">Kratzer</persName> is eminently
                    qualified to undertake this task. Chairman <persName corresp="#p_SGT1"
                        >Seaborg</persName> is willing to make Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KMB1"
                        >Kratzer</persName>’s services available for this purpose.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d228fn2">At the <gloss target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss>’s Information
                        Meeting 777, March 4, <persName corresp="#p_SGT1">Seaborg</persName> and the
                        Commissioners agreed that <persName corresp="#p_KMB1">Kratzer</persName>
                        should be designated Chairman of the Task Force. (Seaborg, <hi rend="italic"
                            >Journal</hi>, Vol. 16, p. 173)</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0594" n="558" xml:id="pg_558"/>
                <p>If you approve this recommendation, I will so notify the members of the Committee
                    of Principals.<note n="3" xml:id="d228fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> initialed his approval on March
                        18.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FAS2">
                            <hi rend="strong">Adrian S. Fisher</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
